21/04/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A court in Belgrade convicted Mladen Obradovic, the leader of ultranationalist group Obraz, for orchestrating riots during Belgrade's Gay Pride Parade last October and sentenced him to two years in prison Wednesday (April 20th).
The 13 other defendants got sentences ranging from eight to 18 months.
More than 140 people were injured in clashes with demonstrators during the event.
(RTS, Tanjug, Beta - 20/04/11)
